glmark2 is an OpenGL 2.0 and ES 2.0 benchmark.

glmark2 is developed by Alexandros Frantzis and Jesse Barker
based on the original glmark benchmark by Ben Smith.

It is licensed under the GPLv3 (see COPYING).

Windows/MSYS2 build notes
=========================
This document contains additional notes for building glmark2
on Windows using MSYS2 and MinGW.

Supported targets:
 * NT6+ x64  (Vista/7/8/10/11 64-bit)
 * NT6+ x86  (Vista/7/8/10/11 32-bit)
 * NT5  x86  (Windows XP)


Prerequisites
-------------
Install MSYS2 from:
    https://www.msys2.org/

Default installation path:
    C:\msys64


Core build dependencies
-----------------------

Required for all targets:
    pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-meson \
              mingw-w64-x86_64-ninja \
              git \
              python


NT6+ x64 build
--------------
Environment:
    MSYS2 MinGW 64-bit (MINGW64)

Dependencies:
    pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-gcc \
              mingw-w64-x86_64-libpng \
              mingw-w64-x86_64-libjpeg-turbo


NT6+ x86 build
--------------
Environment:
    MSYS2 MinGW 32-bit (MINGW32)

Dependencies:
    pacman -S mingw-w64-i686-gcc \
              mingw-w64-i686-libpng \
              mingw-w64-i686-libjpeg-turbo


NT5 / Windows XP build
----------------------
Uses the same i686 toolchain as NT6+ x86, but requires
targeting the legacy Win32 API and static GCC runtime
linking flags.

Typical Meson flags:
    -Dc_args="-D_WIN32_WINNT=0x0501 -DWINVER=0x0501"
    -Dcpp_args="-D_WIN32_WINNT=0x0501 -DWINVER=0x0501"
    -Dc_link_args="-static-libgcc"
    -Dcpp_link_args="-static-libgcc -static-libstdc++"


Runtime DLLs
------------
The provided multi-target build script automatically copies
the required runtime DLLs into each build directory.

DLL layout:

    dlls/
    ├── x64/
    └── x86/
        ├── NT5/
        └── NT6/

Troubleshooting
---------------
If Meson cannot find opengl32, make sure you are building
from a proper MinGW environment.

Do not use the plain MSYS shell.